[3.878146, "o", "es\\n\\nCaptures live outside the project repo, under\\n`~/.pm/sessions/<session-tag>/captures/regression/<test-id>/<timestamp>/`\\non the host. `pm qa captures-path` only knows PR ids — regression\\ncaptures don\\'t have one, so resolve the path yourself (the session-tag\\nprefix is shared with any PR\\'s captures dir if you need to derive it).\\nCaptures are durable on the host but **not** committed to git — don\\'t\\n`git add` them.\\n\\n## QA Regression Test: Smoke\\n\\nJust echo \"hello\" and stop.\\n\\n\\n\\n## Filing Findings\\n\\nFor each issue you observed, file a PR — don\\'t fix it here.\\n\\n- **Bug**: `pm pr add \\'<title>\\' --plan bugs --description \\'<location, repro, expected vs actual>\\'`\\n- **Improvement**: `pm pr add \\'<title>\\' --plan improvements --description \\'<what you noticed and why>\\'`\\n\\nIf a capture from this run demonstrates the finding, point at its\\npath in the description.\\n\\nSkim `pm pr list --plan bugs` / `--plan improvements` first. If a PR\\nfor the same issue exists, append a note instead of f"]
[3.878204, "o", "iling a\\nduplicate: `pm pr note add <pr-id> \\'<short observation>; capture: <path>\\'`.\\n\\nFiling is independent of your verdict for the test.\\n\\n'] (cwd=None, session_key=qa-regression:smoke, session_id=e46296ba...)\r\n\r\n## --plan bugs / --plan improvements in addendum:\r\n"]
[3.879197, "o", "- **Bug**: `pm pr add '\"'\"'<title>'\"'\"' --plan bugs --description '\"'\"'<location, repro, expected vs actual>'\"'\"'`\r\n- **Improvement**: `pm pr add '\"'\"'<title>'\"'\"' --plan improvements --description '\"'\"'<what you noticed and why>'\"'\"'`\r\nSkim `pm pr list --plan bugs` / `--plan improvements` first. If a PR\r\n- **Bug**: `pm pr add '\"'\"'<title>'\"'\"' --plan bugs --description '\"'\"'<location, repro, expected vs actual>'\"'\"'`\r\n- **Improvement**: `pm pr add '\"'\"'<title>'\"'\"' --plan improvements --description '\"'\"'<what you noticed and why>'\"'\"'`\r\nSkim `pm pr list --plan bugs` / `--plan improvements` first. If a PR\r\n00:19:01 INFO  [claude_launcher] launch_claude: cmd=['/home/pm/.local/bin/claude', '--session-id', 'e46296ba-ede6-43d7-86e0-48081ef83f5f', '## Session Context\\n\\nYou are testing against tmux session: pm-qa-rec-test2-cfb5925b\\nThe TUI pane ID is: %2\\n\\nTo interact with this session, use commands like:\\n- pm tui view -s pm-qa-rec-test2-cfb5925b\\n- pm tui send <keys> -s pm-qa-rec-test2-cfb5925b\\n- tmux list-pa"]
[3.879343, "o", "nes -t pm-qa-rec-test2-cfb5925b -F \"#{pane_id} #{pane_width}x#{pane_height} #{pane_current_command}\"\\n- cat ~/.pm/pane-registry/pm-qa-rec-test2-cfb5925b.json\\n\\n## Captures\\n\\nCaptures live outside the project repo, under\\n`~/.pm/sessions/<session-tag>/captures/regression/<test-id>/<timestamp>/`\\non the host. `pm qa captures-path` only knows PR ids — regression\\ncaptures don\\'t have one, so resolve the path yourself (the session-tag\\nprefix is shared with any PR\\'s captures dir if you need to derive it).\\nCaptures are durable on the host but **not** committed to git — don\\'t\\n`git add` them.\\n\\n## QA Regression Test: Smoke\\n\\nJust echo \"hello\" and stop.\\n\\n\\n\\n## Filing Findings\\n\\nFor each issue you observed, file a PR — don\\'t fix it here.\\n\\n- **Bug**: `pm pr add \\'<title>\\' --plan bugs --description \\'<location, repro, expected vs actual>\\'`\\n- **Improvement**: `pm pr add \\'<title>\\' --plan improvements --description \\'<what you noticed and why>\\'`\\n\\nIf a capture from this run demonstrates the find"]
[3.879397, "o", "ing, point at its\\npath in the description.\\n\\nSkim `pm pr list --plan bugs` / `--plan improvements` first. If a PR\\nfor the same issue exists, append a note instead of filing a\\nduplicate: `pm pr note add <pr-id> \\'<short observation>; capture: <path>\\'`.\\n\\nFiling is independent of your verdict for the test.\\n\\n'] (cwd=None, session_key=qa-regression:smoke, session_id=e46296ba...)\r\n\r\n## Triple 2: unknown regression id\r\n$ pm qa regression does-not-exist\r\n"]
